The paper deals with error correction codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The constructions presented in the paper involve multidimensional arrays and clusters, which are concepts related to data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses methods based on colorings of the D-dimensional space, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and can be applied to various fields such as computer vision and machine learning (cs.SI).
